(425721, 'In modern business it is not the crook who is to be feared most, it is the honest man who doesn''t know what he is doing.', 2063, 0), (425722, 'There are two kinds of companies, those that work to try to charge more and those that work to charge less. We will be the second.', 22320, 0), (425723, 'When times are bad is when the real entrepreneurs emerge.', 66592, 0), (425724, 'We need to become good citizens in the global village, instead of competing. What are we competing for - to drive more cars, eat more steaks? That will destroy the world.', 66704, 0), (425725, 'Growing up in eastern Turkey, I was not really involved with the family business - sheep and cow farming, yogurt and cheese making. But I think I learned from my father the unspoken business language or instincts that go back thousands of years.', 66705, 0), (425726, 'Whenever you''re sitting across from some important person, always picture him sitting there in a suit of long red underwear. That''s the way I always operated in business.', 66706, 0), (425727, 'No community values entrepreneurship and small business more than the Hispanic community.', 66707, 0), (425728, 'I''m strong and fearless and not afraid to take risks in business.', 66708, 0), (425729, 'The American people don''t believe politicians. They don''t believe business leaders or Hollywood celebrities or athletes or other supposed role models. And they certainly don''t believe the news media.', 66709, 0), (425730, 'I''ve seen this over and over again: people love it if you step up their experience. No one turns down an upgrade to business class in a plane.', 66710, 0), (425731, 'I''ve never gone into business to make money. Every Virgin product and service has been made into a reality to make a positive difference in people''s lives. And by focusing on the happiness of our customers, we have been able to build a successful group of companies.', 5248, 0), (425732, 'It is indeed true that the stock market can forecast the business cycle.', 66711, 0), (425733, 'It''s a business. If I could make more money down in the zinc mines I''d be mining zinc.', 66712, 0), (425734, 'When steam first began to pump and wheels go round at so many revolutions per minute, what are called business habits were intended to make the life of man run in harmony with the steam engine, and his movement rival the train in punctuality.', 66713, 0), (425735, 'It''s show business. No show, no business.', 66714, 0), (425736, 'When we want to have our own style of living, it is nobody''s business but ours. What we do in private is our private business.', 821, 0), (425737, 'With the growing reliance on social media, we no longer search for news, or the products and services we wish to buy. Instead they are being pushed to us by friends, acquaintances and business colleagues.', 57885, 0), (425738, 'I became a larger than life figure for one reason only. When you''re quoted in the ''Wall Street Journal'', the ''New York Times'', constantly as the expert in the business people assume you''re a lot bigger than you are. And then I had to run like hell to catch up with my own image.', 34972, 0), (425739, 'If I succeed in business but fail as a father, then I''ve failed.', 13187, 0), (425740, 'Now, when it''s time to get down to business, I get down to business.', 66715, 0), (425741, 'The show business has all phases and grades of dignity, from the exhibition of a monkey to the exposition of that highest art in music or the drama which secures for the gifted artists a world-wide fame princes well might envy.', 34868, 0), (425742, 'Men, women, and children who cannot live on gravity alone need something to satisfy their gayer, lighter moods and hours, and he who ministers to this want is, in my opinion, in a business established by the Creator of our nature. If he worthily fulfills his mission and amuses without corrupting, he need never feel that he has lived in vain.', 34868, 0), (425743, 'In business, you can have one massive success that earns $50 million overnight, and that''s it. You''re successful. End of story. But in the music business, you have to keep on doing it.', 13014, 0), (425744, 'The more people you help and the more value you create, the more your business will fly - and the quicker you''ll win.', 1172, 0), (425745, 'Appreciate everything your associates do for the business.', 34844, 0), (425746, 'The chief executive officer is also the chief sales officer. He or she is responsible for the success of the company and making a profit. The closer the CEO is to the everyday selling process, bringing in business, the more successful the company will become.', 11220, 0), (425747, 'During my pre-college years, I went on many trips with my father into the oil fields to visit their operations. On Saturday mornings, I often went with him to visit the company shop. I puttered around the machine, electronics, and automobile shops while he carried on his business.', 61363, 0), (425748, 'I think if we get freedom for women, then they are probably going to do a lot of things that I wish they wouldn''t do. But it seems to me that isn''t our business to say what they should do with it. It is our business to see that they get it.', 64860, 0), (425749, 'Brethren, let us mind our own business - that is, the calling the Lord has called us to - to do everything we can to promote the good of the Cause of Truth, and never ask how big we are, or inquire who we are; but let it be, ''What can I do to build up the Kingdom of God upon the Earth?''', 1854, 0), (425750, 'We''re in the space exploration business, and the outer solar system is a wild, wooly place. We haven''t explored it very well.', 66716, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (425751, 'If you can''t pay for a thing, don''t buy it. If you can''t get paid for it, don''t sell it. Do this, and you will have calm and drowsy nights, with all of the good business you have now and none of the bad. If you have time, don''t wait for time.', 18456, 0), (425752, 'What do I mean by concentration? I mean focusing totally on the business at hand and commanding your body to do exactly what you want it to do.', 24450, 0), (425753, 'The Postal Service''s unmatched ability to reach every household and business in America six days a week is a vital part of the nation''s infrastructure.', 66717, 0), (425754, 'Being tall is an advantage, especially in business. People will always remember you. And if you''re in a crowd, you''ll always have some clean air to breathe.', 1537, 0), (425755, 'In the US, there is basically one party - the business party. It has two factions, called Democrats and Republicans, which are somewhat different but carry out variations on the same policies. By and large, I am opposed to those policies. As is most of the population.', 1955, 0), (425756, 'If you like a person you say ''let''s go into business together.'' Man is a social animal after all, but such partnerships are fraught with danger.', 697, 0), (425757, 'Producing suits me because I have a business mind and a business sensibility. I was a street hustler. I did whatever it took. I sold whatever I could sell. I''m a good organiser.', 13187, 0), (425758, 'Just like any business is a living, breathing thing, an entrepreneur has to be able to adapt over time.', 66654, 0), (425759, 'I have a friend who is very successful in business, and his motto is, ''Don''t do what you can do. Do what only you can do.'' First of all, you have to know what your specific, unique gift is and then you do that... every actor does that but every once in a while an actor plays a part that only they can play.', 12642, 0), (425760, 'If you want to kill any idea in the world, get a committee working on it.', 66718, 0), (425761, 'I never called my work an ''art''. It''s part of show business, the business of building entertainment.', 65266, 0), (425762, 'The beauty of the Internet is there''s a niche market for everything, and if you can focus on it, you can build a sustainable and viable business of it.', 66719, 0), (425763, 'I have no idea what the economics of the movie business is, especially with all the new Amazon, Netflix, Showtime, AMC, SyFy, and HBO series. But I am intrigued with what feels like a new type of show - the six-to-eight-hour movie. It''s a little too long to watch in one setting, but you can watch it over a three- to five-day period.', 66612, 0), (425764, 'It is always sound business to take any obtainable net gain, at any cost and at any risk to the rest of the community.', 52621, 0), (425765, 'Raising children is an incredibly hard and risky business in which no cumulative wisdom is gained: each generation repeats the mistakes the previous one made.', 2059, 0), (425766, 'My kids - even though it''s a family business - they don''t even know what day or time ''Survivor'' is even on. They just know it''s on TiVo.', 10164, 0), (425767, 'All lasting business is built on friendship.', 877, 0), (425768, 'So little done, so much to do.', 62335, 0), (425769, 'An economist''s guess is liable to be as good as anybody else''s.', 1122, 0), (425770, 'You can''t operate a company by fear, because the way to eliminate fear is to avoid criticism. And the way to avoid criticism is to do nothing.', 66720, 0), (425771, 'I like Mr. Gorbachev, we can do business together.', 1945, 0), (425772, 'We must get into the picture business. This is a new industry and a gold mine. it looks like another telephone industry.', 66706, 0), (425773, 'Business today consists in persuading crowds.', 1067, 0), (425774, 'A government, for protecting business only, is but a carcass, and soon falls by its own corruption and decay.', 13866, 0), (425775, 'For the past 32 years, I''ve done nothing outside the entertainment business. I''ve had some real highs and some real lows, but I love the work so much that I never once thought of quitting.', 7252, 0), (425776, 'I believe people who go into politics want to do the right thing. And then they hit a big wall of re-election and the pettiness of politics. In the end, politics gets in the way of the business of people.', 36742, 0), (425777, 'I love my family very much. I wish I could see them a little more often than I do. But we understand because we''re a show business family and we all work.', 646, 0), (425778, 'A government of, by and for the people is obligated to conduct the nation''s business in a manner that respects dissent.', 66721, 0), (425779, 'I wanted to be a writer, to write these stories that would make people see the world in a different way. But I ended up going to business school because I thought I could ultimately get to where I wanted to go faster that way.', 66722, 0), (425780, 'People in business generally have a responsibility to the community. They have to put back into the community from which they take. I think I''ve adopted that all through my life. Caring and sharing are two major fundamentals of life.', 66561, 0), (425781, 'Companies are bought for their revenue, customer base, technology, or people. A few great companies offer all of these, but any valuable business offers one.', 23135, 0), (425782, 'Learning in a face-to-face human community, as humans have evolved to do over hundreds of thousands of years, may always be the ideal - especially in an endeavor that is as relationship-driven as business.', 19589, 0), (425783, 'Hire sales people who are really smart problem solvers, but lack courage, hunger and competitiveness, and your company will go out of business.', 42466, 0), (425784, 'I don''t set out to be connected. My business has allowed me to meet lots of interesting people, some of whom have become friends; but you can''t force it. This terrible word - ''networking'' - I really hate.', 66723, 0), (425785, 'In show business, you had levels. I was at the top of the TV end of it.', 62915, 0), (425786, 'The best defence against mafia business is full declaration of assets and incomes.', 66724, 0), (425787, 'The NFL is a performance-based business, so you should have to perform to earn some of your money. At the same time, I realize that my success isn''t just because of what I do out there.', 66725, 0), (425788, 'Everybody had to go to some college or other. A business college, a junior college, a state college, a secretarial college, an Ivy League college, a pig farmer''s college. The book first, then the work.', 140, 0), (425789, 'CIOs have earned a strategic seat at the table, but now they''ve got to hold that seat - and the only way they can do that is to converse in the language of business value and business benefits and business outcomes that all align perfectly with the strategic agenda of the company.', 66726, 0), (425790, 'Stoutly pro-tax-cut and libertarian on social issues like abortion, Trump is a Republican with the business know-how to turn the country''s economy around.', 66649, 0), (425791, 'Living the past is a dull and lonely business; looking back strains the neck muscles, causing you to bump into people not going your way.', 9616, 0), (425792, 'Modern poets talk against business, poor things, but all of us write for money. Beginners are subjected to trial by market.', 35, 0), (425793, 'I don''t want to do business with those who don''t make a profit, because they can''t give the best service.', 424, 0), (425794, 'Our business in life is not to get ahead of others, but to get ahead of ourselves.', 893, 0), (425795, 'In this business, until you''re known as a monster you''re not a star.', 13058, 0), (425796, 'Politics is not a game. It is an earnest business.', 3621, 0), (425797, 'Young lawyers attend the courts, not because they have business there, but because they have no business.', 944, 0), (425798, 'The successful man is the one who finds out what is the matter with his business before his competitors do.', 54830, 0), (425799, 'War is the business of barbarians.', 1702, 0), (425800, 'There''s always a great deal of business to be transacted in one''s office. There are always visitors it seems to me, an unending stream of them, who come with letters of recommendation, or come actually on substantive business.', 66727, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (425801, 'Ranchers need clean water for their stock, farmers need it for their crops, every employer needs it to stay in business, and every living thing needs it for life... The law needs to be clear to protect water quality and the rights of landowners.', 66728, 0), (425802, 'I have always recognized that the object of business is to make money in an honorable manner. I have endeavored to remember that the object of life is to do good.', 63243, 0), (425803, 'We didn''t know how to run a business, but we had dreams and talent.', 66729, 0), (425804, 'Less emphasis on inventories, I think, may tend to dampen business cycles, because business cycles are typically in the grasp of inventory cycles and heavy industry cycles.', 66730, 0), (425805, 'The business always gets in the way of basketball.', 66731, 0), (425806, 'I think young writers should get other degrees first, social sciences, arts degrees or even business degrees. What you learn is research skills, a necessity because a lot of writing is about trying to find information.', 1425, 0), (425807, 'In 1973, women got 59 cents on the dollar; now we are getting 74 cents on the dollar. In the area of finance and business, we are at 68 cents on the dollar.', 4882, 0), (425808, 'There''s no damn business like show business - you have to smile to keep from throwing up.', 9623, 0), (425809, 'The trouble with movies as a business is that it''s an art, and the trouble with movies as art is that it''s a business.', 5708, 0), (425810, 'All things being equal, people will do business with a friend; all things being unequal, people will still do business with a friend.', 66732, 0), (425811, 'It is the artist''s business to create sunshine when the sun fails.', 1755, 0), (425812, 'Never believe people in this business who say they don''t read what''s written about them.', 66733, 0), (425813, 'Business and growing jobs is about taking risk, sometimes failing, sometimes succeeding, but always striving. It is about dreams. Usually, it doesn''t work out exactly as you might have imagined. Steve Jobs was fired at Apple. He came back and changed the world.', 52321, 0), (425814, 'Because of the economic crisis, China and the United States are bound together. This is a totally new phenomenon, and nobody will fight for ideology anymore. It''s all about business.', 20064, 0), (425815, 'In terms of the technology I use the most, it''s probably a tie between my Blackberry and my MacBook Pro laptop. That''s how I communicate with the rest of the world and how I handle all the business I have to handle.', 28573, 0), (425816, 'If I was in a situation where it wasn''t working and I had a choice with another man, I''m gonna assess it like a business deal: who is the better person for me?', 66734, 0), (425817, 'It''s the uncertainty, the challenge and the willingness to put it all on the line that draws a lot of people to climb mountains. That can also apply to a lot of other challenges in life, whether it''s running for office, starting a family, going to grad school or taking all of your cash and assets and starting a business.', 66728, 0), (425818, 'I began painting well before I started doing comedy. In fact, when I came out of the war in 1946, I enrolled in art school in Dayton, Ohio. I painted for three years, and then show business took hold.', 60426, 0), (425819, 'We live in a world where there are a hell of a lot of new inputs that need to be factored in to your business. It used to be just about your employees and your customers. Now there are all the issues about global warming, about sustainability, about ethics and now about gender and the distribution of wealth.', 66735, 0), (425820, 'If you are in business, you are not enjoying. You are working.', 66736, 0), (425821, 'It''s weird because my parents don''t really understand my business. I get fan mail all day long, but if a piece happens to get to their house, they''re like, ''Oh, my 